There is enough natural yeast on the skin of the fruit for the juice to ferment without interference. When it comes to bottling, a spoonful of sugar in each of the spring-clip bottles ensures that the cider has fizz. Sitwell opened one to prove his point, and shot foam three metres over the grass, like a winning racing driver with a bottle of champagne. He looked nonplussed. “That wasn’t meant to happen.”
